<title>MALAYSIA: Malaysia bans nitrofuran usage in chicken feed.</title>
<headline>Malaysia bans nitrofuran usage in chicken feed.</headline>
<dateline>KUALA LUMPUR 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Malaysia has banned the use of nitrofuran, an antibiotic, in chicken feed and veterinary applications because it believes the drug could cause cancer, the health ministry said on Thursday.</p>
<p>&quot;It is hoped that livestock breeders and feedmillers will abide by the laws and respect the cabinet decision in the interest of consumer safety,&quot; Health Minister Chua Jui Meng was quoted as saying by the national Bernama news agency.</p>
<p>Chua said offenders could face a two-year prison sentence and a maximum fine of 5,000 ringgit ($2000).</p>
<p>&quot;The ban takes effect immediately,&quot; he added.</p>
</text>
